	<a name="features"></a>
	<h2 class="divider">Features</h2>
	<p>Collect and update data in the field, log your current location, and put the data you capture to work so you can make more informed and timely decisions. 
	Use maps anywhere to ground-truth your data, make observations, and respond to events. 
	You'll improve the efficiency of your field workforce and the accuracy of your GIS.</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>Download maps to your device and work offline.</li>
	<li>Use GPS to create and update map data.</li>
	<li>Collect points, lines, and area features.</li>
	<li>Fill out easy-to-use map-driven forms.</li>
	<li>Find places and get directions.</li>
	<li>Track and report areas you visited.</li>
	</ul>

        <a name="systemRequirements"></a>
        <h2 class="divider">System requirements</h2>

        <p>There are certain device requirements to run Collector, as well as requirements on the data that is used within the app. Collector is supported in a number of languages.</p>


        <h3>Data requirements</h3>
        <p>To use your maps in Collector, you must have an ArcGIS organizational account. Your maps can include data from ArcGIS Online, Portal for ArcGIS, and ArcGIS for Server.</p>


        <h3>Device requirements</h3>
        <table><tr><td valign="top" width="320px;"><h4 class="icon-android">Android</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Android 4.0 (Ice Cream Sandwich) or later</li>
          <li>ARMv7 or x86 processor</li>
          <li>OpenGL ES 2.0 support</li>
          <li>Precise location (GPS and network-based) support</li>
        </ul></td>
        <td valign="top"><h4 class="icon-apple">iOS</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>iOS 7 or later</li>
          <li>iPhone, iPad, iPod touch</li>
        </ul></td><tr></table>


        <h3>Supported languages</h3>
        <p>Arabic, Czech, Danish, Dutch, English, Estonian (<span class="icon-android"/>), Finnish, French, German, Hebrew, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Latvian (<span class="icon-android"/>), Lithuanian (<span class="icon-android"/>), Norwegian, Polish, Portuguese (Brazil), Portuguese (Portugal), Romanian, Russian, Simplified Chinese, Spanish, Swedish, Thai, and Turkish.</p>
        <p>The language used by the app is determined by your device's language setting.</p>


        <a name="whatsNew"></a>
        <h2 class="divider">What's new</h2>
        <p>Collector for ArcGIS 10.3 was released in January 2015 on Android and March 2015 on iOS. It includes the following enhancements:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Ability to view and edit related records</li>
          <li>Support for taking additional data offline, including the following:
	    <ul>
	      <li>Hosted tile layers</li>
	      <li>Editable versioned data (from ArcGIS 10.3 for Server or later)</li>
	      <li>Layers with editor tracking</li>
	      <li>Layers with limited feature service capabilities, including add-only and update-only editing</li>
	    </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Various bug fixes and improvements, including NIM101011, NIM101989, NIM102096, NIM103498, NIM103525, NIM103549, NIM103836, NIM104130, and BUG-000083110</li>
        </ul>

	<a name="sneakPeek"></a>
	<h2 class="divider">Sneak peek</h2>
	<p>Today, Collector is a great app for collecting and editing your data in the field. But there is more to come!
	The following outlines where we'd like to take this app:</p>
	
	<ul>
	  <li>Support for Windows and Windows Phone</li>
	  <li>Smarter data collection forms</li>
	  <li>Support for external GNSS receivers</li>
	  <li>More tools for planning offline field operations</li>
	  <li>Data collection with offsets</li>
	  <li>Integration of peripherals (laser range finders, bar code scanners, and so on)</li>
	</ul>	
	
	<p>Share your <a href="http://ideas.arcgis.com/">ideas</a>, and <a href="mailto:Collector4ArcGIS@esri.com?subject=Collector%20feedback">send us your feedback</a>.</p>
		
